metadata.title: Herring Spawn Data (Canada)

creators.name: Ocean Canada - Pacific Region, Pacific Biological Station

metadata.description:
Length and width of spawn (meters), dates and locations of spawn, vegetation types, number of layers of eggs on each vegetation type.  Data collected from the west coast of British Columbia, Canada.  Until 1987, spawns were surveyed using the 'surface survey' method.  After 1987, most spawns surveyed by SCUBA diving.

  [ A TCODE project ]
